label: Term
definition: A word or phrase used to represent a concept  that follows a specific naming convention suitable for machine use

label: Label
definition: The preferred lexical label for a resource in a given language

label: Class Name
definition: Class name (without preferred namespace prefix) a term (rdf:Property) belongs to

label: Class IRI
definition: An internationalized resource identifier used to unique identify a class or the class a term belongs to

label: Material Category
definition: The semantic boundaries of a concept within which a concept is valid within the context of a dwc:Material
notes: Intended to be used in conjuncture with dwc:materialCategory or dwc:materialEntityType

label: Definition
definition: A descriptive statement that supplies a complete explanation of the intended meaning of the type and serves to differentiate it from related concepts.

label: examples
definition: Supplies an example of concept usage

label: Usage
definition: Information on how a term is to be used.

label: source
definition: List of resources (bibliographic citations, URLs, and general descriptive statements) used for the construction of a term and/or its supporting metadata (e.g., definition, usage note).

label: RDF Type
definition: Property that states the type or category a term belongs within the class-property data structure defined in the RDF Schema

label: datatype
definition: Identifies the type of data, which has a bearing on the acceptable data values, the operations that can be performed with the data, and the ways in which the data are stored.
notes: A subset of the values in the source scheme are utilized by TDWG standards

label: Required
definition: Specifies that when a resource is utilized  a value must be supplied

label: Note
definition: A general note, for any purpose not covered elsewhere in the vocabulary

label: editorial_notes
definition: Notes for an editor, translator or maintainer of the vocabulary.

label: namespace
definition: The preferred namespace prefix to use when using terms from this vocabulary

label: namespace_iri
definition: The preferred namespace URI to use when using terms from this vocabulary

label: Term IRI
definition: An internationalized resource identifier used to unique identify a resource (term).

label: Modified
definition: Date on which the resource was changed and serves as the version identifier
notes: Scope of the modification is a single defined term

label: Created
definition: Date on which the term was published as part of a ratified standard

label: Document Modified
definition: Date on which the vocabulary was modified and last published
notes: Changes associated with a formal republication of a standard generate a new modified date
